Organisers of Zimbabwe President Robert Mugabe s mega birthday party will this weekend splash out $800000 (R10.5m) on a lavish celebration.Mugabe turned 93 yesterday and will celebrate his birthday where British imperialist Cecil John Rhodes is buried.The bash has become an annual event and will take place at the Matopo National Park, an hour s drive from Bulawayo, Zimbabwe s second largest city.Last year, the bash cost R13.1m.During an interview, Mugabe admitted he also stashes cash under his pillow like many Zimbabweans who fear they may not be able to access their savings if they bank them.Zimbabwe s cash squeeze worsens every day and the payment of civil servants salaries is regularly delayed.MTHOKOZISI DUBE